						<b>CASH FOR HONOURS</b>
<br>
=20
<br>
Just before 3pm this afternoon, the Cash for Honours story moved into a new=
 realm. The Metropolitan Police announced they have handed a 216 page long =
file of evidence to the Crown Prosecution Service.=20=20
<br>

<br>
After an inquiry that lasted more than a year, during which time 136 people=
 were interviewed, we now await the CPS's judgement on whether charges will=
 be brought and against whom.  With elections in the coming weeks - and the=
 impending departure of Tony Blair - the timing of any prosecution could ha=
ve significant consequences.  Michael Crick will be making his assessment.
<br>
=20
<br>
<b>FRENCH ELECTION</b>
<br>

<br>
The French presidential elections are shaping up into a classic Right/Left =
battle between the two leading candidates, the former Interior Minister Nic=
olas Sarkozy and the socialist Segolene Royal.=20
<br>

<br>
After a campaign in which the two of them criticised each other for talking=
 about themselves, the voters have two polling rounds to decide which (and =
it could just be a matter of degrees) is better equipped to pull the countr=
y out of the economic and cultural doldrums.=20=20
<br>

<br>
The first round campaign concludes as we're on air this evening with pollin=
g on Sunday. Allan Little is in Paris and we'll host a debate between proxi=
es for Sarkosy and Royal here in the studio.
<br>
=20
<br>
<b>WELSH ELECTIONS</b>
<br>
=20=20
<br>
And looking ahead to elections here - Michael Crick has been noseying about=
 the Welsh valleys to find out just how much pressure Labour is under in on=
e of their heartlands.
<br>

<br>

<br>

